messages.content:
THOUGHT: The miscompile persists because in at least one transform path, a new select is created without preserving the original select’s fast-math flags (nnan, nsz). Changing all call sites was too invasive. A robust, centralized fix is to ensure InstCombine copies FMF from the old instruction to the new one when replacing instructions. I will modify InstructionCombining to copy fast-math flags whenever a new FPMathOperator (including SelectInst on FP types) replaces an old FPMathOperator. This avoids widespread code changes and ensures FMF preservation across all transforms.

```bash
applypatch << 'PATCH'
*** Begin Patch
*** Update File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstructionCombining.cpp
@@
   if (I == &Inst)
     return nullptr;

   // Users may expect the result of a combine to be in the same block as
   // Inst. Insert the new instruction into the entry block of the function
   // to inform.
   if (I->getParent() == nullptr) {
     if (isa<Argument>(Inst.getOperand(0)))
       I->insertBefore(&*Inst.getFunction()->getEntryBlock().getFirstInsertionPt());
     else
       I->insertBefore(&Inst);
   }

+  // Preserve fast-math flags if both old and new are FP math operators (e.g., FP select).
+  if (auto *OldFPO = dyn_cast<FPMathOperator>(&Inst))
+    if (auto *NewFPO = dyn_cast<FPMathOperator>(I)) {
+      // Copy FMF from the old instruction to the new one.
+      FastMathFlags FMF = OldFPO->getFastMathFlags();
+      cast<Instruction>(NewFPO)->setFastMathFlags(FMF);
+    }
+
   // Patch the new instruction into the place of the old one and replace all
   // uses.
   I->takeName(&Inst);
   Worklist.RegisterReplace(&Inst, I);
   replaceInstUsesWith(Inst, I);
*** End Patch
PATCH
```

